column5: Well headed out of bbp on simcoe today. Tried a few different depths from 65-110ft marked quite a few fish at all locations. Moved one last time around 11 and found some active whities. Between 11:30 and 1:00 i iced three and lost several others. Quite a nice day out there. Had to cross a few pressure cracks to get out the but the were fairly solid and we had no real issues. Gonna give it one last try tomorrow.
Hey WTG man nice whities good to see all those Simcoe reports.  Won't be long and cabin fever will set in.
nice going seems most of us got fish on simcoe today
I'm really looking forward to tomorrow morning.  I'll be out off of Willow beach.
